\title{Polynomials form a vector space}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{example}
\meta{source}{[[axler-1996-linear]] Example 1.23}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] Example 4.1.5}

\p{Let #{\FF[z]} be the set of all polynomial with coefficients in #{\FF} and in unknown #{z}. Then defining #{(p+q)(z)=p(z)+q(z)} and #{(ap)(z)=ap(z)} for any #{a\in\FF} and #{p,q\in\FF[z]} forms vector addition and scalar multiplication.}